      "content_html": "<img src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/steam.jpg?fit=1200%2C800&amp;quality=60&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/steam.jpg?fit=1200%2C800&amp;quality=60&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/06/25/steam-summer-sale-is-back-with-witcher-3-at-4-cyberpunk-under-20.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Steam Summer Sale is back with Witcher 3 at $4, Cyberpunk under $20\"><img alt=\"Alberto Garcia Guillen / Shutterstock.com\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/steam.jpg?fit=1200%2C800&amp;quality=60&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"1200\" /></a><p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Truly, the turning of the seasons can be best measured by the rotating Steam sales. More than anything else, it feels like <em>these</em> are the factor most responsible for Valve becoming so powerful they feel like they can <a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/06/23/valves-steam-machine-will-run-you-at-least-a-thousand-dollars.html\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" target=\"_blank\">charge a thousand dollars</a> for their underpowered cube: whoever you are, and wherever you are on the planet, you can get games for cheap on Steam. &#8212; <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/06/25/steam-summer-sale-is-back-with-witcher-3-at-4-cyberpunk-under-20.html\">Read the rest </a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/06/25/steam-summer-sale-is-back-with-witcher-3-at-4-cyberpunk-under-20.html\">Steam Summer Sale is back with Witcher 3 at $4, Cyberpunk under $20</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://boingboing.net\">Boing Boing</a>.</p>",
